Industries: Biotechnology, Health Care, Health Diagnostics, Medical
Description: Redox Diagnostics is a company that uses diagnostic tests to search for Alzheimers Disease in patients.
Full Description: Redox Diagnostics is focused on creating an early diagnostic assay for Alzheimer’s disease. The enzyme targeted in this assay is cytochrome c oxidase (CO; Complex IV) of the mitochondrial electron transport chain. This specific deficiency has been found in brain and in platelets from AD patients, as well as in other peripheral tissues (that are somewhat less accessible; e.g., muscle) by numerous independent labs around the world, including us. Our finding of a significant decrease in the function of CO in platelet mitochondria isolated from subjects with MCI solidified the hypothesis that interference with mitochondrial function is an early and detectable systemic event in AD pathophysiology which can be leveraged as a biomarker of the disease. While the mitochondrial assays used in that earlier work have shown themselves to be relatively laborious and variable, each requiring mitochondrial isolation from the target cells as a first step, our early work with this technology has revealed a new methodology for the application of reliable tissue histochemistry to cells in suspension, thus enabling the accurate assessment of mitochondrial enzyme activity without confounding mitochondrial isolation, greatly improving sensitivity and ease-of-use, and reducing cost.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: JKL Software’s Total Office Data Diagnostic Software.
Full Description: JKL Software’s Total Office Data Diagnostic Software, also known as TODDS, is the premier software for practitioners of TMD/TMJ, sleep apnea, and ortho. The software is designed to handle what regular dental office software doesn’t – required data for these specialities, medical necessity for treatment, and billing requirements. While there are many software programs today that handle your patient’s general dental care, there is not a single comprehensive solution that handles your TMD/TMJ, sleep apnea, and ortho patients. Some programs do nothing more than generate letters, others only store imaging and photographs; most of these require extra user input and don’t save your data for future reference. TODDS maintains all patient information, handles examination data and imaging, stores unlimited photographs, generates PR correspondence with all involved parties, assembles data from multiple examinations into cohesive reporting, and stores it all to be pulled up at will. TODDS is an evidence-based medicine (EBM) and electronic healthcare record (EHR) solution.

Description: WineLog is a new take on mixing social networking and user generated content to help users keep track and rate the wines they've tried
Full Description: WineLog is a new take on mixing social networking and user generated content to help users keep track and rate the wines they've tried while getting recommendations from others. In specific, WineLog proposes custom wine recommendations based on user preferences.  The idea is quite simple: Most people base their wine decisions on magazine reviews and ratings. The problem with this approach is that general reviews and ratings do not take specific wine preferences into account. WineLog's recommendation system allows users to compare their recorded comments and ratings to those of other WineLog users. For example, if two users both highly rate one brand of chardonnay, then it is likely that they will also enjoy other similar types of chardonnay. Their respective WineLogs display the chardonnays highly rated by the other user and proposes them as wines that they may also enjoy. The more wines users enter into their log, the more specific their wine recommendations will be. Competitors include [Snooth](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/snooth), [TasteVine](http://www.tastevine.com/), [Vinorati](http://www.vinorati.com/), and the very 1.0 [WineSearcher](http://www.wine-searcher.com/).
